@* Unlike UseSecurityHeaders in WebApplicationExtensions.cs, which only applies during Blazor Server
   and Blazor WebAssembly Pre-Rendering, this component works across all Interactive Blazor
   rendering modes (Server, WebAssembly, WebAssembly Standalone, Auto and Hybrid).
   Because it enforces a stricter Content-Security-Policy, it is not enabled by default.
   To activate it, add <SecurityHeaders /> inside AppShell.razor *@

<HeadContent>
    <meta name="referrer" content="strict-origin-when-cross-origin">
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy" content="@CspContent">
</HeadContent>